{
  "texts": [
    "Twisted Principal BundlesIn this section we define a class of manifolds with local symmetries that will serve as the underlying spaces for the Ricci solitons we construct.",
    "These spaces generalise the notion of a principal bundle, allowing for more phenomena to occur.",
    "Our treatment is based on [Lot20] (see also [Lot10, §4.1]).Definition 2.1.",
    "Let N be a connected Lie group and B a smooth manifold.",
    "A twisted principal N-bundle is a fibre bundle π: M → B with fibre N and structure group contained in Aut(N) δ ⋉ N L. (Here, the subscript δ means that the group Aut(N) is endowed with the discrete topology, and N L ≤ Diff(N) denotes the action of N on itself by left multiplication."
  ]
}